pgwSharedIpPoolStatsTable.name: pgwSharedIpPoolStatsTable
pgwSharedIpPoolStatsTable.description: A table listing the statistics for all shared IP pools which are served by the PGW.

pgwSharedIpPoolStatsEntry.name: pgwSharedIpPoolStatsEntry
pgwSharedIpPoolStatsEntry.description: A conceptual row listing the statistics for each shared IP pool which is served by the PGW.

pgwSharedIpPoolIndex.name: pgwSharedIpPoolIndex
pgwSharedIpPoolIndex.description: A number representing each shared IP pool whose statistics are generated.

pgwSharedIpPoolName.name: pgwSharedIpPoolName
pgwSharedIpPoolName.description: The identifier of a shared IP pool.

pgwAvailableAddressesInSharedIpPool.name: pgwAvailableAddressesInSharedIpPool
pgwAvailableAddressesInSharedIpPool.description: The number of available IP addresses in a shared IP pool.

pgwAddressesInQuarantineInSharedIpPool.name: pgwAddressesInQuarantineInSharedIpPool
pgwAddressesInQuarantineInSharedIpPool.description: The number of IP addresses that are in quarantine in a shared IP pool

ggsnFbcInitiatedDeactivation.name: ggsnFbcInitiatedDeactivation
ggsnFbcInitiatedDeactivation.description: The number of bearer deactivations initiated by the SACC functionality.

ggsnFbcApplicationTransactionPps.name: ggsnFbcApplicationTransactionPps
ggsnFbcApplicationTransactionPps.description: Number of transactions toward pre-paid server.

ggsnFbcApplicationTransactionPrs.name: ggsnFbcApplicationTransactionPrs
ggsnFbcApplicationTransactionPrs.description: Number of transactions toward policy/rate server.

ggsnVersion.name: ggsnVersion
ggsnVersion.description: The revision of this application, blank if unknown or unavailable.

ggsnInstalled.name: ggsnInstalled
ggsnInstalled.description: The value of sysUpTime when the application was last restarted. Zero if unknown.

ggsnStatReportTime.name: ggsnStatReportTime
ggsnStatReportTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the global statistics report is generated.

ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContexts.name: ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContexts
ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContexts.description: The number of active PDP contexts on this GGSN. Incremented when a PDP context is activated and a GTP response has been sent to the SGSN. Decremented when a PDP context is deactivated.

ggsnNbrOfSubscribers.name: ggsnNbrOfSubscribers
ggsnNbrOfSubscribers.description: The number of subscribers, uniquely identified by IMSI, currently serviced by this GGSN. Incremented on transmission of a PDP context response with request accepted for an IMSI (which previously did not have a PDP context active). Decremented when the last PDP context for that IMSI has been deleted. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnNbrOfSubscribersMean.name: ggsnNbrOfSubscribersMean
ggsnNbrOfSubscribersMean.description: The mean number of subscribers serviced by this GGSN. Incremented on transmission of a PDP context response with request accepted for an IMSI (which previously did not have a PDP context active). Decremented when the last PDP context for that IMSI has been deleted. The mean number of subscribers is calculated over five samples taken over a 15 minute period. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnNbrOfTftFilters.name: ggsnNbrOfTftFilters
ggsnNbrOfTftFilters.description: The number of Traffic Flow Template filters on this GGSN.

ggsnControlLoad.name: ggsnControlLoad
ggsnControlLoad.description: Weighted PDP context load in control.

ggsnPayloadLoad.name: ggsnPayloadLoad
ggsnPayloadLoad.description: This gauge keeps track of the weighted load on the node for the payload part. The gauge is used for the new load balancing scheme. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContextsIpv6.name: ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContextsIpv6
ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContextsIpv6.description: The number of active IPv6 PDP contexts on this GGSN.

ggsnNeighborSolicitationRcv.name: ggsnNeighborSolicitationRcv
ggsnNeighborSolicitationRcv.description: The number of neighbor solicitation requests received by GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnNeighborSolicitationRsp.name: ggsnNeighborSolicitationRsp
ggsnNeighborSolicitationRsp.description: The number of neighbor solicitation responses from GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnRouterSolicitationRcv.name: ggsnRouterSolicitationRcv
ggsnRouterSolicitationRcv.description: The number of router solicitation requests received by GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnRouterSolicitationRsp.name: ggsnRouterSolicitationRsp
ggsnRouterSolicitationRsp.description: The number of router solicitation responses from GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnL2tpActiveTunnels.name: ggsnL2tpActiveTunnels
ggsnL2tpActiveTunnels.description: The number of currently active L2TP tunnels.

ggsnL2tpMaxActiveTunnels.name: ggsnL2tpMaxActiveTunnels
ggsnL2tpMaxActiveTunnels.description: The max number of active L2TP tunnels since last restart.

ggsnL2tpActiveSessions.name: ggsnL2tpActiveSessions
ggsnL2tpActiveSessions.description: The number of currently active L2TP sessions.

ggsnL2tpMaxActiveSessions.name: ggsnL2tpMaxActiveSessions
ggsnL2tpMaxActiveSessions.description: The max number of active L2TP sessions since last restart.

ggsnChgEncodedCdrs.name: ggsnChgEncodedCdrs
ggsnChgEncodedCdrs.description: The number of successfully encoded CDRs on this GGSN.

ggsnChgFailedEncodedCdrs.name: ggsnChgFailedEncodedCdrs
ggsnChgFailedEncodedCdrs.description: The number of unsuccessfully encoded CDRs on this GGSN.

ggsnChgGeneratedFtpCdrs.name: ggsnChgGeneratedFtpCdrs
ggsnChgGeneratedFtpCdrs.description: The number of CDRs generated for FTP.

ggsnChgGeneratedGtppCdrs.name: ggsnChgGeneratedGtppCdrs
ggsnChgGeneratedGtppCdrs.description: The number of CDRs generated for GTP prime.

ggsnChgGtppLogCdrs.name: ggsnChgGtppLogCdrs
ggsnChgGtppLogCdrs.description: The number of GTP prime CDRs stored in the charging log.

ggsnChgGtppAttemptedCdrsSend.name: ggsnChgGtppAttemptedCdrsSend
ggsnChgGtppAttemptedCdrsSend.description: The number sending attempts of CDRs generated for GTP prime.

ggsnChgGtppCdrsSendFailure.name: ggsnChgGtppCdrsSendFailure
ggsnChgGtppCdrsSendFailure.description: The number sending failures of CDRs generated for GTP prime.

ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassConversati.name: ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassConversational
ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassConversati.description: The number of active PDP contexts per Traffic Class, conversational.

ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassStreaming.name: ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassStreaming
ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassStreaming.description: The number of active PDP contexts per Traffic Class, streaming.

ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassInteractiv.name: ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassInteractive
ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassInteractiv.description: The number of active PDP contexts per Traffic Class, interactive.

ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassBackground.name: ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassBackground
ggsnNbActivePdpPerTrafficClassBackground.description: The number of active PDP contexts per Traffic Class, background.

ggsnRadiusAuthenticationFailure.name: ggsnRadiusAuthenticationFailure
ggsnRadiusAuthenticationFailure.description: The number of failed RADIUS Authentication procedures.

ggsnRadiusAccountingFailure.name: ggsnRadiusAccountingFailure
ggsnRadiusAccountingFailure.description: The number of failed RADIUS Accounting procedures.

ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContextsWlan.name: ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContextsWlan
ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContextsWlan.description: The number of active WLAN PDP contexts on this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsn3gdtActiveContexts.name: ggsn3gdtActiveContexts
ggsn3gdtActiveContexts.description: The number of active 3GDT PDP contexts on this GGSN.

ggsn3gdtTotalCompletedEstablishment.name: ggsn3gdtTotalCompletedEstablishment
ggsn3gdtTotalCompletedEstablishment.description: The number of total completed 3GDT PDP context establishments on this GGSN.

ggsn3gdtTotalAttemptedEstablishment.name: ggsn3gdtTotalAttemptedEstablishment
ggsn3gdtTotalAttemptedEstablishment.description: The number of total attempted 3GDT PDP context establishments on this GGSN.

ggsn3gdtErrorHandling.name: ggsn3gdtErrorHandling
ggsn3gdtErrorHandling.description: The number error indications from RNC.

gn3gdtTotalCompletedEstablishment.name: gn3gdtTotalCompletedEstablishment
gn3gdtTotalCompletedEstablishment.description: The number of total completed 3GDT PDP context establishments on this GGSN.

gn3gdtTotalAttemptedEstablishment.name: gn3gdtTotalAttemptedEstablishment
gn3gdtTotalAttemptedEstablishment.description: The number of total attempted 3GDT PDP context establishments on this GGSN.

gn3gdtErrorHandling.name: gn3gdtErrorHandling
gn3gdtErrorHandling.description: The number error indications from RNC.

ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContextsIpv4v6.name: ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContextsIpv4v6
ggsnNbrOfActivePdpContextsIpv4v6.description: The number of active IPv4v6 PDP contexts on this GGSN.

ggsnAttemptedActivation.name: ggsnAttemptedActivation
ggsnAttemptedActivation.description: The number of PDP context activation procedures initiated by the MS on this GGSN. Incremented each time a Create PDP Context Request that is not silently discarded is received by the GGSN. This means the SNMP counter incremented each time a Create PDP Context Response is sent back to the SGSN with cause value Request Accepted or Request Rejected. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedDeactivation.name: ggsnAttemptedDeactivation
ggsnAttemptedDeactivation.description: The number of PDP context deactivation procedures initiated by the MS on this GGSN. Incremented each time a Delete PDP Context Request is received at this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedSelfDeactivation.name: ggsnAttemptedSelfDeactivation
ggsnAttemptedSelfDeactivation.description: The number of PDP context deactivation procedures initiated by this GGSN. Incremented each time this GGSN attempts to delete a context. Increases for all types of internal deletes. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedUpdate.name: ggsnAttemptedUpdate
ggsnAttemptedUpdate.description: The number of PDP context updates attempted on this GGSN. Incremented each time an Update PDP Context Request is received at this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedTimeDeactivation.name: ggsnAttemptedTimeDeactivation
ggsnAttemptedTimeDeactivation.description: The number of PDP context deactivation procedures initiated by this GGSN due to the idle supervision function.

ggsnAttemptedManualDeactivation.name: ggsnAttemptedManualDeactivation
ggsnAttemptedManualDeactivation.description: The number of PDP context deactivation procedures initiated by this GGSN due to manual user command. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivation.name: ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivation
ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivation.description: The number of secondary PDP context activation procedures initiated by the MS on this GGSN. All GPRS session management statistics except ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivation, ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivation, ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivationIpv6, and ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivationIpv6 will accumulate all pdp contexts, that is both secondary and primary. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedActivationIpv6.name: ggsnAttemptedActivationIpv6
ggsnAttemptedActivationIpv6.description: The number of IPv6 PDP context activation procedures initiated by the MS on this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivationIpv6.name: ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivationIpv6
ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivationIpv6.description: The number of secondary IPv6 PDP context activation procedures initiated by the MS on this GGSN. All GPRS session management statistics except ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivation, ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivation, ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivationIpv6, and ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivationIpv6 will accumulate all pdp contexts, that is both secondary and primary. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedActivationWlan.name: ggsnAttemptedActivationWlan
ggsnAttemptedActivationWlan.description: The number of WLAN PDP context activation procedures initiated by the MS on this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedActivationConversational.name: ggsnAttemptedActivationConversational
ggsnAttemptedActivationConversational.description: The total number of attempted primary and secondary PDP context activation procedures with traffic class conversational on this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedActivationStreaming.name: ggsnAttemptedActivationStreaming
ggsnAttemptedActivationStreaming.description: The total number of attempted primary and secondary PDP context activation procedures with traffic class streaming on this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedActivationInteractive.name: ggsnAttemptedActivationInteractive
ggsnAttemptedActivationInteractive.description: The total number of attempted primary and secondary PDP context activation procedures with traffic class interactive on this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedActivationBackground.name: ggsnAttemptedActivationBackground
ggsnAttemptedActivationBackground.description: The total number of attempted primary and secondary PDP context activation procedures with traffic class background on this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedActivationDiscarded.name: ggsnAttemptedActivationDiscarded
ggsnAttemptedActivationDiscarded.description: The total number of attempted primary and secondary PDP context activations that are discarded on this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnAttemptedActivationIpv4v6.name: ggsnAttemptedActivationIpv4v6
ggsnAttemptedActivationIpv4v6.description: The number of IPv4v6 PDP context activation procedures initiated by the MS on this GGSN. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnCompletedActivation.name: ggsnCompletedActivation
ggsnCompletedActivation.description: The number of successfully completed PDP context activation procedures initiated by an MS. Incremented each time a Create PDP Context Response is sent back to an SGSN with cause value Request Accepted.

ggsnCompletedDeactivation.name: ggsnCompletedDeactivation
ggsnCompletedDeactivation.description: The number of successfully completed PDP context deactivation procedures initiated by an MS. Note: This counter can not be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnCompletedSelfDeactivation.name: ggsnCompletedSelfDeactivation
ggsnCompletedSelfDeactivation.description: The number of successfully completed PDP context deactivation procedures initiated by the GGSN. Note: This counter can not be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnCompletedUpdate.name: ggsnCompletedUpdate
ggsnCompletedUpdate.description: The number of successfully completed PDP context update procedures initiated by an MS. Incremented each time an Update PDP Context Response is sent back to an SGSN with cause value Request Accepted.

ggsnIdleTimeoutDeactivation.name: ggsnIdleTimeoutDeactivation
ggsnIdleTimeoutDeactivation.description: The number of successfully completed PDP context deactivation procedures initiated by the GGSN due to the idle supervision function. Note: The PDP context is supervised for the time it has been idle, without actual payload.

ggsnCompletedManualDeactivation.name: ggsnCompletedManualDeactivation
ggsnCompletedManualDeactivation.description: The number of successfully completed PDP context deactivation procedures initiated by the GGSN due to manual user command.

ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivation.name: ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivation
ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivation.description: The number of successfully completed secondary PDP context activation procedures initiated by an MS. Note: All GPRS session management statistics except ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivation, ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivation, ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivationIpv6, and ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivationIpv6 count all PDP contexts, both secondary and primary.

ggsnSessionTimeoutDeactivation.name: ggsnSessionTimeoutDeactivation
ggsnSessionTimeoutDeactivation.description: The number of successfully completed PDP context deactivation procedures initiated by the GGSN due to the duration supervision function. Note: The PDP context is supervised for the time it has been active, irrespective of the actual payload.

ggsnCompletedActivationIpv6.name: ggsnCompletedActivationIpv6
ggsnCompletedActivationIpv6.description: The number of successfully completed IPv6 PDP context activation procedures initiated by an MS.

ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivationIpv6.name: ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivationIpv6
ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivationIpv6.description: The number of successfully completed secondary IPv6 PDP context activation procedures initiated by an MS. Note: All GPRS session management statistics except ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivation, ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivation, ggsnAttemptedSecondaryActivationIpv6, and ggsnCompletedSecondaryActivationIpv6 count all PDP contexts, both secondary and primary.

ggsnCompletedActivationWlan.name: ggsnCompletedActivationWlan
ggsnCompletedActivationWlan.description: The number of successfully completed WLAN PDP context activation procedures initiated by an MS. Note: This counter can not be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnCompletedActivationConversational.name: ggsnCompletedActivationConversational
ggsnCompletedActivationConversational.description: The number of successfully completed primary and secondary PDP context activation procedures with traffic class conversational. Note: This counter can not be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnCompletedActivationStreaming.name: ggsnCompletedActivationStreaming
ggsnCompletedActivationStreaming.description: The number of successfully completed primary and secondary PDP context activation procedures with traffic class streaming. Note: This counter can not be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnCompletedActivationInteractive.name: ggsnCompletedActivationInteractive
ggsnCompletedActivationInteractive.description: The number of successfully completed primary and secondary PDP context activation procedures with traffic class interactive. Note: This counter can not be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnCompletedActivationBackground.name: ggsnCompletedActivationBackground
ggsnCompletedActivationBackground.description: The number of successfully completed primary and secondary PDP context activation procedures with traffic class background. Note: This counter can not be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnCompletedActivationIpv4v6.name: ggsnCompletedActivationIpv4v6
ggsnCompletedActivationIpv4v6.description: The number of successfully completed IPv4v6 PDP context activation procedures initiated by an MS. Note: This counter can not be retrieved by CLI.

ggsnFailedActivation.name: ggsnFailedActivation
ggsnFailedActivation.description: The number of failed PDP context activation procedures initiated by an MS. Incremented each time a Create PDP Context Response is sent back to an SGSN with cause value Request Rejected.

ggsnGtpUplinkPackets.name: ggsnGtpUplinkPackets
ggsnGtpUplinkPackets.description: Total number of uplink control plane GTP packets processed by the GGSN or PGW. Incremented when an uplink GTP packet is received over the Gn control plane.

ggsnGtpUplinkBytes.name: ggsnGtpUplinkBytes
ggsnGtpUplinkBytes.description: Total number of bytes for the uplink control plane GTP packets processed by the GGSN or PGW. Incremented when an uplink GTP packet is received over the Gn control plane.

ggsnGtpDownlinkPackets.name: ggsnGtpDownlinkPackets
ggsnGtpDownlinkPackets.description: Total number of downlink control plane GTP packets processed by the GGSN or PGW. Incremented when a downlink packet is sent over the Gn control plane.

ggsnGtpDownlinkBytes.name: ggsnGtpDownlinkBytes
ggsnGtpDownlinkBytes.description: Total number of bytes for the downlink control plane GTP packets processed by the GGSN or PGW. Incremented when a downlink packet is sent over the Gn control plane.

ggsnGtpControlPacketDrops.name: ggsnGtpControlPacketDrops
ggsnGtpControlPacketDrops.description: The total number of GTP-C control packets that have been dropped by the node.

ggsnGtpVerUnsupPacketsReceived.name: ggsnGtpVerUnsupPacketsReceived
ggsnGtpVerUnsupPacketsReceived.description: The number of Version Unsupported responses received by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpVerUnsupPacketsSent.name: ggsnGtpVerUnsupPacketsSent
ggsnGtpVerUnsupPacketsSent.description: The number of Version Unsupported responses sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpEchoReqReceived.name: ggsnGtpEchoReqReceived
ggsnGtpEchoReqReceived.description: The number of GTP echo requests received by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpEchoReqSent.name: ggsnGtpEchoReqSent
ggsnGtpEchoReqSent.description: The number of GTP echo requests sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpEchoRespReceived.name: ggsnGtpEchoRespReceived
ggsnGtpEchoRespReceived.description: The number of GTP echo responses received by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpEchoRespSent.name: ggsnGtpEchoRespSent
ggsnGtpEchoRespSent.description: The number of GTP echo responses sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpCreateReqReceived.name: ggsnGtpPdpCreateReqReceived
ggsnGtpPdpCreateReqReceived.description: The number of PDP Create requests received by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpCreateRespSent.name: ggsnGtpPdpCreateRespSent
ggsnGtpPdpCreateRespSent.description: The number of PDP Create responses sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpUpdateReqReceived.name: ggsnGtpPdpUpdateReqReceived
ggsnGtpPdpUpdateReqReceived.description: The number of PDP update requests received by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpUpdateReqSent.name: ggsnGtpPdpUpdateReqSent
ggsnGtpPdpUpdateReqSent.description: The number of PDP update requests sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpUpdateRespReceived.name: ggsnGtpPdpUpdateRespReceived
ggsnGtpPdpUpdateRespReceived.description: The number of PDP update responses received by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpUpdateRespSent.name: ggsnGtpPdpUpdateRespSent
ggsnGtpPdpUpdateRespSent.description: The number of PDP update responses sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpDeleteReqReceived.name: ggsnGtpPdpDeleteReqReceived
ggsnGtpPdpDeleteReqReceived.description: The number of PDP delete requests received by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpDeleteReqSent.name: ggsnGtpPdpDeleteReqSent
ggsnGtpPdpDeleteReqSent.description: The number of PDP delete requests sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpDeleteRespReceived.name: ggsnGtpPdpDeleteRespReceived
ggsnGtpPdpDeleteRespReceived.description: The number of PDP delete responses received by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpDeleteRespSent.name: ggsnGtpPdpDeleteRespSent
ggsnGtpPdpDeleteRespSent.description: The number of PDP delete responses sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpRequestsAccepted.name: ggsnGtpRequestsAccepted
ggsnGtpRequestsAccepted.description: The number of GTP requests accepted by the GGSN. Incremented each time a Create PDP Context Response, Update PDP Context Response or Delete PDP Context Response is sent back to an SGSN with cause value Request Accepted.

ggsnGtpNbrOfTunnels.name: ggsnGtpNbrOfTunnels
ggsnGtpNbrOfTunnels.description: The number of currently active GTP tunnels on the GGSN. Each primary PDP context is counted twice for signaling tunnel and payload tunnel, and each secondary PDP context is counted once for payload tunnel only, as they share signaling tunnels with their primary PDP contexts.

ggsnGtpNbrOfCreatedTunnels.name: ggsnGtpNbrOfCreatedTunnels
ggsnGtpNbrOfCreatedTunnels.description: The total number of GTP tunnels that have been created on the GGSN. Each primary PDP context is counted twice for signaling tunnel and payload tunnel, and each secondary PDP context is counted once for payload tunnel only, as they share signaling tunnels with their primary PDP contexts.

ggsnGtpPdpInitiateContextActivationRespR.name: ggsnGtpPdpInitiateContextActivationRespReceived
ggsnGtpPdpInitiateContextActivationRespR.description: The number of Initiate PDP Context Activation Responses received by the GGSN from an SGSN.

ggsnGtpPdpInitiateContextActivationReqSe.name: ggsnGtpPdpInitiateContextActivationReqSent
ggsnGtpPdpInitiateContextActivationReqSe.description: The number of Initiate PDP Context Activation Requests sent by the GGSN to an SGSN.

ggsnGtpv0PdpCreateReqReceived.name: ggsnGtpv0PdpCreateReqReceived
ggsnGtpv0PdpCreateReqReceived.description: The number of GtpV0 PDP Create requests received by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorIndicationReceived.name: ggsnGtpErrorIndicationReceived
ggsnGtpErrorIndicationReceived.description: The number of Error Indications received by the node (aggregate of error indications received by the GTP-U).

ggsnGtpErrorIndicationSent.name: ggsnGtpErrorIndicationSent
ggsnGtpErrorIndicationSent.description: The number of Error Indications sent by the node (aggregate of error indications sent by the GTP-U). The GGSN may send an Error Indication to the SGSN or RNC if no PDP context exists or the PDP context is inactive for a received GTP Packet Data Unit (G-PDU).

ggsnGtpErrorInvalidRequestFormat.name: ggsnGtpErrorInvalidRequestFormat
ggsnGtpErrorInvalidRequestFormat.description: The number of GTP invalid request format errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorResourcesUnavailable.name: ggsnGtpErrorResourcesUnavailable
ggsnGtpErrorResourcesUnavailable.description: The number of GTP resources unavailable errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorDynAddrUnavailable.name: ggsnGtpErrorDynAddrUnavailable
ggsnGtpErrorDynAddrUnavailable.description: The number of GTP dynamic address unavailable errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorMemoryUnavailable.name: ggsnGtpErrorMemoryUnavailable
ggsnGtpErrorMemoryUnavailable.description: The number of GTP memory not available errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorApnUnknown.name: ggsnGtpErrorApnUnknown
ggsnGtpErrorApnUnknown.description: The number of GTP APN invalid errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorPdpAddrUnknown.name: ggsnGtpErrorPdpAddrUnknown
ggsnGtpErrorPdpAddrUnknown.description: The number of GTP PDP address unknown errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorAuthenticationFailed.name: ggsnGtpErrorAuthenticationFailed
ggsnGtpErrorAuthenticationFailed.description: The number of GTP authentication failed errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorSystemFailure.name: ggsnGtpErrorSystemFailure
ggsnGtpErrorSystemFailure.description: The number of GTP system failure errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorTftSemanticError.name: ggsnGtpErrorTftSemanticError
ggsnGtpErrorTftSemanticError.description: The number of GTP TFT semantic errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorTftSyntaxError.name: ggsnGtpErrorTftSyntaxError
ggsnGtpErrorTftSyntaxError.description: The number of GTP TFT syntax errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorPackFiltSemantError.name: ggsnGtpErrorPackFiltSemantError
ggsnGtpErrorPackFiltSemantError.description: The number of semantic packet filter errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorPackFiltSyntaxError.name: ggsnGtpErrorPackFiltSyntaxError
ggsnGtpErrorPackFiltSyntaxError.description: The number of packet filter syntax errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorMandatoryIEMissing.name: ggsnGtpErrorMandatoryIEMissing
ggsnGtpErrorMandatoryIEMissing.description: The number of errors sent by the GGSN indicating that a mandatory information element was missing.

ggsnGtpErrorMandatoryIEInvalid.name: ggsnGtpErrorMandatoryIEInvalid
ggsnGtpErrorMandatoryIEInvalid.description: The number of errors sent by the GGSN indicating that a mandatory information element was invalid.

ggsnGtpErrorOptionalIEInvalid.name: ggsnGtpErrorOptionalIEInvalid
ggsnGtpErrorOptionalIEInvalid.description: The number of errors sent by the GGSN indicating that an optional information element was invalid.

ggsnGtpErrorReferenceInexistent.name: ggsnGtpErrorReferenceInexistent
ggsnGtpErrorReferenceInexistent.description: The number of cause codes 'Context Not Found' and 'Non Existent' sent as response to the following operations: -Create PDP context -Update PDP context -Delete PDP context

ggsnGtpErrorServiceUnsupported.name: ggsnGtpErrorServiceUnsupported
ggsnGtpErrorServiceUnsupported.description: The number of service unsupported errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorInvalidRequestFormatUpd.name: ggsnGtpErrorInvalidRequestFormatUpd
ggsnGtpErrorInvalidRequestFormatUpd.description: The number of GTP invalid update request format errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorInvalidRequestFormatDel.name: ggsnGtpErrorInvalidRequestFormatDel
ggsnGtpErrorInvalidRequestFormatDel.description: The number of GTP invalid delete request format errors sent by the GGSN.

ggsnGtpErrorSystemFailureUpd.name: ggsnGtpErrorSystemFailureUpd

ggsnApnAttemptedActivation.name: ggsnApnAttemptedActivation
ggsnApnAttemptedActivation.description: The total number of attempted PDP context activations for this APN. Opposite to ggsnAttemptedActivation, the ggsnApnAttemptedActivation is incremented even when a Create PDP Context Request is silently discarded. Note1: If logical APN selection or RADIUS Assisted APN Selection (RAAS), or both are used, the counter is incremented on the chosen physical APN. If RAAS is used, and the RADIUS server does not reply or replies with an incorrect answer, the counter is incremented on the APN, using RAAS. Note2: When the SGSN resends the activation request, it is counted as two attempts on APN level but as only one attempt on node level. (This happens when the primary RADIUS server is unavailable.)

ggsnApnAttemptedSelfDeactivation.name: ggsnApnAttemptedSelfDeactivation

ggsnApnCompletedActivation.name: ggsnApnCompletedActivation
ggsnApnCompletedActivation.description: The total number of completed PDP context activations per APN. Number of completed activations doesn't necessarily match the number of attempts for the same APN. The APN may have changed after the attempt was made due to logical APN or RADIUS-assisted APN selection. The sum of all ggsnApnAttemptedActivation should match the sum of ggsnApnCompletedActivation (and failed) over all APNs.

ggsnGtpuUserUplinkDrops.description: The number of uplink (GTP-U) packets dropped by this GGSN-U PIC. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI. Packets can be dropped for a number of reasons, including the following: The packet is classified as unauthorized after packet inspection The packet is an IPv6 link-local packet There are errors in the GTP header There is no PDP context There are general IP header faults No SGSN entry is found IP-in-IP encapsulation is missing for packet inspection IP-in-IP encapsulation provides wrong packet length The IP version is other than IPv4 or IPv6 No GGSN-U/I application is available The packet cannot be forwarded to an GGSN-U/I application for classification The packet cannot be sent A certain type of IP traffic (IPv4/IPv6) is not allowed A bandwidth limitation is defined for the APN, and the limit is exceeded The packet is a broadcast message from an MS The IP packet source address does not match the IP address assigned to the MS by the GGSN There is no free memory left in U-PIC

ggsnGtpuUserDownlinkDrops.description: The number of downlink (GTP-U) packets dropped by this GGSN-U PIC. Note: This counter cannot be retrieved by CLI.
